  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nOn a Spring-Boot very easy are able to see information about build and git branch \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/115703261/208839485-0050d1a1-4bb0-45d2-803d-4f2fd39258fd.png)\r\n\r\nOn Quarkus we do not yet have this possibility this is mainly needed when projects have test environments to help for a team know what version and latest build was deployed, especially if Your build may be deployed manually by anyone ( QA/PO )\r\n\r\nSpring-Boot build info example: https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/2.1.13.RELEASE/maven-plugin/examples/build-info.html\r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\nSuggest to implement this functionaly under exising quarkus-boom (default's) \r\nor\r\nMay be implemented similar plugin to https://plugins.gradle.org/plugin/com.gorylenko.gradle-git-properties\r\n",
